    "recap_headline": "Stephen F. Austin",
    "recap_text": "COLLEGE STATION, Texas \u2013\nThe Stephen F. Austin baseball team was unable to generate offense in their 14-1 ballgame\u00a0at #22 Texas A&M in a midweek matchup on Tuesday, March 10.\nThe Lumberjacks were able to keep close with the Aggies, letting up three runs in the first by SFA, giving Texas A&M a 3-0 lead for three innings.\nNoah O'Farrell\nkept the Aggie offense guessing in the second and third innings, striking out one batter and collecting five outs with the backup of his Lumberjack defense. In the top of the fourth,\nMark Henning\nclosed the 3-0 gap with a solo shot to center field to bring the Aggie lead to two runs, before Blake Binderup launched his own solo home run in the bottom of the frame.\nJonathan Valdez\nkept the fifth inning quiet against the Aggies, allowing no runs with the efforts of the SFA defense, with Texas A&M holding onto a close 4-1 lead to close out the frame. The sixth inning consisted of the Aggies compiling 11 runs, followed by a scoreless top of the seventh to end the night in a 14-1 defeat for SFA.\nWP:\nEthan Darden (2-0): 1.1 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 1 K, 4 BF\nLP:\nNoah O'Farrell\n(0-1): 4.0 IP, 5 H, 4 R, 1 K, 19 BF\nPOSTGAME NOTES:\nThe Aggies collected their 16th win of the all-time series against SFA.\nTexas A&M moves to 15-1 on the season.\nMark Henning\ntallies his second home run of the season in back-to-back games\nCermodrick Bland\nfound the hit column against the Aggies, after going hitless in his previous two games during the Lamar series\nNoah O'Farrell\npitches a season-high of four innings in his third start, tying his season high in strikeouts\nSFA reaches the 150-strikeout benchmark on the season, adding two more today to total at 151.\nThe 'Jacks ERA levels off at 6.05 on the season\nThe Lumberjacks made consistent contact against Aggie pitching, striking out only four times as a team, their third-lowest total this season\nNEXT UP\nSFA moves to 11-7 on the year as the Lumberjacks now look forward to their Southland series with the Lions of Southeastern Louisiana for the 45th meeting. The Lions will host SFA starting on Friday, March 13, and will conclude the three-game series on Sunday, March 15.\nSECURE YOUR SEATS TODAY\nSingle game tickets\nfor all SFA baseball home games are available now. Fans interested in purchasing season ticket packages can secure their seats\nhere\n. Don't miss out on all the exciting action from Pilgrim's Park this season!\nTHE JACKS HAVE GONE MOBILE\nSFA Athletics' newest mobile phone application is designed to bring Lumberjack fans closer to the action than ever before. Available now on both the App Store and Google Play, the new SFA Athletics app delivers schedules, scores, rosters, news, ticket access, and exclusive content right to your phone. Fans can also receive push notifications, so they never miss a moment of the action. Download now:\nOfficial SFA Athletics App\n.\nFOLLOW THE JACKS\nFor all the latest information on SFA baseball, visit\nSFAjacks.com\n. For up-to-the-minute updates, follow the Jacks on\nX\n,\nInstagram\nand\nFacebook\n.\n#AxeEm x #LogByLog"
